Problem Statement



Ethan is writing a program to identify prime numbers. A prime number is a number greater than 1 that has no positive divisors other than 1 and itself.



Your task is to help Ethan write a program that reads an integer and checks whether it is a prime number or not.

Input format :
The input consists of a integer representing N.

Output format :
The output consists of string representing "Prime", if the number is a prime number.

The output consists of string representing "Not Prime" if the number is not a prime number.



Refer to the sample output for the formatting specifications.

Code constraints :
1 ≤ n ≤ 10,000

Sample test cases :
Input 1 :
10
Output 1 :
Not Prime
Input 2 :
3
Output 2 :
Prime



// You are using Java
import java.util.*;
public class Main{
    public static void main(String [] args){
        Scanner sd=new Scanner (System.in);
        int n=sd.nextInt();
        if(n%2!=0&&n%n==0){
            System.out.println("Prime");
        }else{
            System.out.println("Not Prime");
        }
    }
}
